### ==========================================
### CONFIGURATION
### ==========================================
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api

### ==========================================
### 1. AUTHENTICATION – Get tokens for all roles
### ==========================================

### 1.1 Login as Citizen
# @name citizenLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "citizen@test.com",
  "password": "Test@1234"
}
@citizenToken = {{citizenLogin.response.body.token}}

### 1.2 Login as OrgAdmin
# @name orgAdminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@eep.com.et",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}
@orgAdminToken = {{orgAdminLogin.response.body.token}}

### 1.3 Login as DeptAdmin
# @name deptAdminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "water.supply@aawsa.gov.et",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}
@deptAdminToken = {{deptAdminLogin.response.body.token}}

### 1.4 Login as SysAdmin (optional, for org creation)
# @name sysAdminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "sysadmin@complaint.gov",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}
@sysAdminToken = {{sysAdminLogin.response.body.token}}

### ==========================================
### 2. CITIZEN – Create a base complaint (for duplicate detection)
### ==========================================
@orgId = 65f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1   # Replace with actual org ID

# @name baseComplaint
POST {{baseUrl}}/complaints
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Water leak near my house",
  "description": "There is a continuous water leak from the main pipe on Bole Road. It has been flooding the street for 3 days.",
  "organizationId": "{{orgId}}"
}
@baseComplaintId = {{baseComplaint.response.body.complaint.id}}

### ==========================================
### 3. CITIZEN – Create a potential duplicate complaint (similar to base)
### ==========================================
# @name duplicateComplaint
POST {{baseUrl}}/complaints
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Water pipe burst on Bole Road",
  "description": "A pipe burst is causing water to flow on the road. It's been leaking for days and wasting water.",
  "organizationId": "{{orgId}}"
}
@dupComplaintId = {{duplicateComplaint.response.body.complaint.id}}

### ==========================================
### 4. CITIZEN – Create a spam complaint
### ==========================================
# @name spamComplaint
POST {{baseUrl}}/complaints
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Buy cheap watches!!!",
  "description": "Get luxury watches at 90% discount. Limited offer! Click here: http://spam.com",
  "organizationId": "{{orgId}}"
}
@spamComplaintId = {{spamComplaint.response.body.complaint.id}}

### ==========================================
### 5. CITIZEN – Create a low-confidence (ambiguous) complaint
### ==========================================
# @name ambiguousComplaint
POST {{baseUrl}}/complaints
Authorization: Bearer {{citizenToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "General issue",
  "description": "Something is wrong but I don't know what.",
  "organizationId": "{{orgId}}"
}
@ambComplaintId = {{ambiguousComplaint.response.body.complaint.id}}

### ==========================================
### 6. RUN AI MODERATION ON EACH COMPLAINT
### ==========================================

### 6.1 Moderate base complaint (should be normal, high confidence, assign department)
# @name moderateBase
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/moderate
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "complaintId": "{{baseComplaintId}}"
}

### 6.2 Moderate duplicate complaint (should be marked as duplicate of base)
# @name moderateDup
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/moderate
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "complaintId": "{{dupComplaintId}}"
}

### 6.3 Moderate spam complaint (isSpam=true, status=Rejected)
# @name moderateSpam
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/moderate
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "complaintId": "{{spamComplaintId}}"
}

### 6.4 Moderate ambiguous complaint (low confidence, status=Manual Review)
# @name moderateAmb
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/moderate
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "complaintId": "{{ambComplaintId}}"
}

### ==========================================
### 7. CHECK NOTIFICATIONS TRIGGERED BY AI
### ==========================================

### 7.1 OrgAdmin notifications (should see REVIEW_NEEDED for spam and low confidence)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}

### 7.2 DeptAdmin notifications (should see COMPLAINT_ASSIGNED for base complaint)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{deptAdminToken}}

### ==========================================
### 8. VERIFY COMPLAINT STATUSES AFTER AI MODERATION
### ==========================================

### 8.1 Base complaint – status should be "Submitted" (or "In Progress" if auto-assigned)
GET {{baseUrl}}/complaints/{{baseComplaintId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}

### 8.2 Duplicate complaint – status should reflect duplicate (still "Submitted" but duplicateOf set)
GET {{baseUrl}}/complaints/{{dupComplaintId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}

### 8.3 Spam complaint – status should be "Rejected"
GET {{baseUrl}}/complaints/{{spamComplaintId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}

### 8.4 Ambiguous complaint – status should be "Manual Review"
GET {{baseUrl}}/complaints/{{ambComplaintId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}

### ==========================================
### 9. (Optional) OrgAdmin can override AI decisions
### ==========================================
### Example: Override spam to not spam
PUT {{baseUrl}}/complaints/{{spamComplaintId}}/override
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isSpam": false,
  "status": "Submitted",
  "comment": "False positive, restoring"
}

### ==========================================
### 6.5 Verify AI department assignment for base complaint
### ==========================================

### Fetch the base complaint after moderation to see department
# @name getBaseComplaint
GET {{baseUrl}}/complaints/{{baseComplaintId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}

### Expected: complaint.department should NOT be null, and should match WATER_SUPPLY or similar
### (Manual check: look for "department" field in response)

### ==========================================
### 7. CHECK NOTIFICATIONS TRIGGERED BY AI
### ==========================================

### 7.1 OrgAdmin notifications (REVIEW_NEEDED for spam / low confidence)
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{orgAdminToken}}

### 7.2 DeptAdmin notifications – should include COMPLAINT_ASSIGNED for base complaint
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{deptAdminToken}}
### ==========================================
### END OF AI MODERATION TESTS
### ==========================================